#: pronounceit/scoring/feedback.py:31
msgid ""
"Spectral analysis shows that the sound is different from the reference. Try "
"to listen carefully to the reference and imitate."
msgstr ""

#: pronounceit/scoring/feedback.py:35
msgid ""
"The sound is close to the reference but can be improved. Focus on the "
"precision of articulation."
msgstr ""

#: pronounceit/scoring/feedback.py:41
msgid ""
"The pitch pattern differs markedly. Pay attention to intonation and stress."
msgstr ""

#: pronounceit/scoring/feedback.py:45
msgid ""
"Intonation can be improved. Listen to the melody in the reference "
"pronunciation."
msgstr ""

#: pronounceit/scoring/feedback.py:52
msgid ""
"The vowels need to be adjusted. Check the position of your tongue and lips."
msgstr ""

#: pronounceit/scoring/feedback.py:57
msgid ""
"The vowels are close but can be refined. Think about mouth opening and "
"tongue position."
msgstr ""

#: pronounceit/scoring/feedback.py:76
msgid ""
"Excellent! Your pronunciation is very close to the reference. Well done!"
msgstr ""

#: pronounceit/scoring/feedback.py:78
msgid "Good pronunciation! A few small adjustments can make it even better."
msgstr ""

#: pronounceit/scoring/feedback.py:80
msgid "Approved pronunciation. Keep practicing to improve accuracy."
msgstr ""

#: pronounceit/scoring/feedback.py:82
msgid ""
"Pronunciation needs more practice. Listen carefully to the reference and try "
"again."
msgstr ""

#: pronounceit/scoring/feedback.py:84
msgid "Try it again! Listen to the reference and focus on one sound at a time."
msgstr ""

#: pronounceit/scoring/feedback.py:101
msgid "Swedish has many vowels. e.g. 'hus' /hʉːs/ vs 'huss' /hɵs/."
msgstr ""

#: pronounceit/scoring/feedback.py:105
msgid ""
"Svenskan har ordaccenter (accent 1 och accent 2). Tonhöjdsmönstret är "
"viktigt för ordets betydelse."
msgstr ""

#: pronounceit/scoring/feedback.py:114
msgid ""
"German vowels have a clear distinction between tense and non-tense. T.ex. /"
"iː/ i 'Miete' vs /ɪ/ i 'Mitte'."
msgstr ""

#: pronounceit/scoring/feedback.py:123
msgid ""
"French nasal vowels require air to be released through the nose. Practice "
"with /ɑ̃/ in 'dans' och /ɛ̃/ i 'vin'."
msgstr ""
